# 79. Word Search

**Platform:** LeetCode  
**Difficulty:** Medium  
**Topic:** Backtracking + DFS (Grid Traversal)

---

## 🧠 Problem Statement

Given a 2D board of characters and a string `word`, return `true` if the word exists in the grid.

The word can be constructed from letters of sequentially adjacent cells, where:
- Adjacent cells are horizontally or vertically neighboring.
- The same cell may NOT be used more than once.

---

## 💡 Intuition

This is a classic **Backtracking on Grid** problem.

Key idea:
- Try starting from every cell.
- If first character matches → run DFS.
- Explore all 4 directions.
- Mark cell as visited to avoid reuse.
- Backtrack (restore cell) after recursion.

Why Backtracking?
Because we must explore all possible paths and undo choices when a path fails.

---

## 🎯 Approach

1. Traverse each cell of the board.
2. If `board[i][j] == word.charAt(0)`:
   - Start DFS from that cell.
3. In DFS:
   - If `index == word.length()` → return true.
   - Check boundary conditions.
   - Check character match.
   - Mark cell as visited.
   - Explore 4 directions.
   - Restore the cell (backtrack).

---

## 🔁 DFS Logic

At position `(i, j)`:
- If out of bounds → return false
- If character mismatch → return false
- If index reached end → return true
- Mark visited
- Try:
  - Down
  - Up
  - Right
  - Left
- Restore cell
- Return result

---

## ✅ Java Implementation

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean exist(char[][] board, String word) {
        int rows = board.length;
        int cols = board[0].length;

        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
                if (board[i][j] == word.charAt(0)) {
                    if (dfs(board, word, i, j, 0)) {
                        return true;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    private boolean dfs(char[][] board, String word, int i, int j, int index) {

        if (index == word.length()) {
            return true;
        }

        if (i < 0 || j < 0 || i >= board.length || j >= board[0].length
                || board[i][j] != word.charAt(index)) {
            return false;
        }

        char temp = board[i][j];
        board[i][j] = '#';  // mark visited

        boolean found =
                dfs(board, word, i + 1, j, index + 1) ||
                dfs(board, word, i - 1, j, index + 1) ||
                dfs(board, word, i, j + 1, index + 1) ||
                dfs(board, word, i, j - 1, index + 1);

        board[i][j] = temp;  // backtrack

        return found;
    }
}
